{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015A6XuEiyZrcUpiZsf7S3jF","type":"tool_result","content":"  5880→- **7 tech debt items deferred** from epic 16 alone. These are all LOW but accumulate.\n  5881→- **5 pre-existing BATS test failures** unrelated to current work — these create noise in verification reports.\n  5882→\n  5883→### 6. Lessons Learned\n  5884→\n  5885→**Repeat:**\n  5886→- Code review before verification catches real bugs (8 found, all fixed)\n  5887→- Unit-testable tier classification avoids Docker dependency entirely\n  5888→- Verification tier tags in story files enable correct dispatch\n  5889→\n  5890→**Avoid:**\n  5891→- Running full sessions when sprint is complete — need an early-exit gate\n  5892→- Running npm test multiple times per subagent — capture once, reference output\n  5893→- Launching retrospectives that are longer than the session they cover\n  5894→- Letting sprint-state.json drift from git commits without automatic reconciliation\n  5895→\n  5896→### 7. Action Items\n  5897→\n  5898→#### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n  5899→- [ ] Resolve sprint-state.json persistence bug — stories should not revert after being committed as `done`\n  5900→- [ ] Clean up `1-1-foo` test story ($24.35 wasted)\n  5901→\n  5902→#### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n  5903→- [ ] Add no-op session short-circuit to orchestrator (skip full state scan when all stories done)\n  5904→- [ ] Block TodoWrite via hook enforcement (111 calls, $15.24 wasted)\n  5905→- [ ] Fix 5 pre-existing BATS test failures in `all_tasks_complete` suite\n  5906→- [ ] Attribute \"unknown\" orchestrator costs to specific stories or phases\n  5907→\n  5908→#### Backlog (Track but Not Urgent)\n  5909→- [ ] 7 tech debt items from epic 16 (all LOW — barrel re-export, line refs, priority test, section ordering, string brittleness, legacy terminology x2)\n  5910→- [ ] Improve subagent prompt to instruct single test run with output capture\n  5911→- [ ] Add HarnessState `opensearch` field definition (from 15-4 tech debt)\n  5912→\n  5913→#### Cost Optimization\n  5914→- [ ] **Subagent test capture:** Instruct subagents to run `npm test` once and cache output ($2-5 savings per story, ~$150-370 over full sprint)\n  5915→- [ ] **Combine vitest runs:** Use `--coverage` on single run instead of test + coverage separately\n  5916→- [ ] **No-op retro template:** Auto-generate minimal retro for sessions with 0 stories completed (~$3/session saved)\n  5917→- [ ] **Early orchestrator exit:** When `sprint.done === sprint.total`, exit without scanning individual stories (~$5-10/session saved)\n  5918→- [ ] **Read-once policy:** Subagent instructions should mandate reading files once and referencing cached content\n  5919→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013dDNJbQFtW3qEuC2XdsVop","session_id":"bce7c985-d530-400a-91ed-b7a2185ee37f","uuid":"de471b02-449f-4e34-a2fb-85dc8f37298e","timestamp":"2026-03-28T13:31:56.683Z"}
